Figure Caption: XRD patterns from the AlCoCrFeNi alloy in as-cast condition and after different heat treatments (a) and in the region of two theta, ranging between 40 and 49 at higher resolution (b).

Back-scattered electron image illustrating the dendritic macro-structure of the as-cast condition of AlCoCrFeNi alloy far from the chill. The dendrite was composed of a dendrite core DC (dark areas) and an inter-dendritic region, ID (bright areas).
Back-scattered electron images illustrating the micro-structure of the as-cast condition of AlCoCrFeNi alloy of the DC (a) and ID (b) regions.
Back-scattered electron images illustrating the DC micro-structure of AlCoCrFeNi alloy after exposure to different heat treatment temperatures for 3 h a) 850 b) 975, c) 1100 and d-e) 1200 °C.
Backs-scattered electron images illustrating the ID micro-structure of AlCoCrFeNi alloy after exposure to different heat treatment temperatures for 3 h a) 850 b) 975, c) 1100 and d-e) 1200 °C.
Engineering compressive stress/strain curves for the AlCoCrFeNi alloy in the as-cast condition and after different heat treatments.
Back-scattered electron images illustrating crack propagation after fracture during the compressive test at different temperatures a-c) 850 °C, d-e) 975 °C.
